This paper proposes a routing protocol for mobile ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to networking and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and optimization, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper discusses the expected density of progress, which is a measure of network performance, indicating that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
